00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,083
Throw it in the garbage.

255
00:14:28,625 --> 00:14:30,791
Uh... Okay.

256
00:14:30,875 --> 00:14:34,291
[ARISA] You know, not everybody
around here likes you.

257
00:14:34,375 --> 00:14:36,083
Don't you forget it.

258
00:14:36,166 --> 00:14:37,083
I won't.

259
00:14:37,166 --> 00:14:38,458
[ICHIBAN]
Oh-ho-ho-ho.

260
00:14:38,541 --> 00:14:40,583
Tell me: when you say
not everybody around here

261
00:14:40,666 --> 00:14:43,041
likes Otomi, are you
referring to yourself?

262
00:14:45,750 --> 00:14:47,208
Ugh, shut up, loser.

263
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,000
Oh, come on.

264
00:14:51,083 --> 00:14:53,208
I can't believe somebody like
her would be in second place.

265
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,625
What a load of bull-crap.

266
00:14:54,708 --> 00:14:56,291
Second place in what?

267
00:14:56,375 --> 00:15:00,500
Oh! Just the 42nd Miss
Meisei Popularity Contest!

268
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:03,625
But! You've won first
place by a huge margin.

269
00:15:03,708 --> 00:15:05,500
Two years in a row.

270
00:15:05,583 --> 00:15:07,791
So that's why she's
holding a grudge against me.

271
00:15:07,875 --> 00:15:10,875
I've never heard anything so
ridiculous in my entire life.

272
00:15:12,208 --> 00:15:14,208
That's not the only
reason why, though.

273
00:15:14,291 --> 00:15:15,875
[AKAI]
Hey! Tachibana!

274
00:15:16,958 --> 00:15:18,125
[AKAI]
Did you get the memo?

275
00:15:18,208 --> 00:15:19,500
All the class reps are
meeting up during lunch

276
00:15:19,583 --> 00:15:21,000
in meeting room two.

277
00:15:21,083 --> 00:15:22,416
Just letting you know.

278
00:15:27,250 --> 00:15:29,291
Crap! The survey!

279
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,750
I haven't even tallied up
the results yet!

280
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,916
Oh, don't worry,
I already took care of that,

281
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,291
but would you mind
double checking my work?

282
00:15:36,375 --> 00:15:38,541
Be happy to. Thanks, Akai.

283
00:15:38,625 --> 00:15:41,625
Listen, buddy.
I think you're a good guy.

284
00:15:41,708 --> 00:15:44,166
But, not everybody
around here likes you,

285
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:46,583
and if you know what's good
for you, you won't forget it.

286
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:47,958
'Kay...?

287
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:50,125
Natsuno, please.

288
00:15:50,208 --> 00:15:52,833
Well then, I'll see you
at lunch in meeting room two.

289
00:15:52,916 --> 00:15:54,041
Yeah.

290
00:15:57,375 --> 00:15:58,958
The runner up for Miss Meisei.

291
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,375
She has a crush on that guy.

292
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:01,791
[gasps]

293
00:16:01,875 --> 00:16:03,625
Back when they
were second years,

294
00:16:03,708 --> 00:16:05,166
they were both class
reps and got to spend

295
00:16:05,250 --> 00:16:09,083
a lot of time together.
But this year, all that changed.

296
00:16:09,166 --> 00:16:10,708
She can't be mad at me for that!

297
00:16:10,791 --> 00:16:14,208
How is it my fault? The homeroom
teacher asked and I said yes!

298
00:16:14,291 --> 00:16:15,666
Well, you should just
resign yourself to the fact

299
00:16:15,750 --> 00:16:18,958
that she hates you.
What a shame.

300
00:16:19,041 --> 00:16:20,541
Being too popular is a curse.

301
00:16:20,625 --> 00:16:22,541
So many enemies.

302
00:16:22,625 --> 00:16:24,541
[NARRATOR]
You're one to talk!

303
00:16:24,625 --> 00:16:26,125
What? Did you say something?

304
00:16:26,208 --> 00:16:28,125
No, I didn't say anything!

305
00:16:28,208 --> 00:16:30,750
[ICHIBAN]
Hmm. Huh, well that was weird.

306
00:16:32,041 --> 00:16:33,375
[PLAYER 07G]
Ready.

307
00:16:33,458 --> 00:16:38,041
--Fight! Fight! Fight!
--[PLAYERS] Fight! Fight! Fight!

308
00:16:38,125 --> 00:16:40,000
[grunting

309
00:16:43,708 --> 00:16:45,916
[TADASHI]
Excuse me, Manager?

310
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,333
Question.

311
00:16:47,416 --> 00:16:48,916
Why aren't you letting
Tachibana throw in the bullpen

312
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,291
with the other guys?

313
00:16:50,375 --> 00:16:53,125
My rule is new club members
run before they play.

314
00:16:53,208 --> 00:16:54,958
They need to build
their endurance.

315
00:16:56,125 --> 00:16:58,375
[OOYAMA] Tachibana
may be my old buddy's kid,

316
00:16:58,458 --> 00:16:59,791
but I don't play favorites.

317
00:16:59,875 --> 00:17:02,125
--[TAKESHITA grunts]
--[OOYAMA] Be patient.

318
00:17:02,208 --> 00:17:05,166
He'll be ready to step
onto the mound by fall.

319
00:17:05,250 --> 00:17:08,208
I'm just curious.
You seen Touma pitch?

320
00:17:08,291 --> 00:17:10,583
Not yet. But don't worry.

321
00:17:10,666 --> 00:17:14,083
I have heard the rumors, so my
expectations are pretty high.

322
00:17:14,166 --> 00:17:15,458
You should see him.

323
00:17:15,541 --> 00:17:16,916
Listen, kid.

324
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,333
I've got a winning strategy
of rotating our pitchers.

325
00:17:20,416 --> 00:17:22,458
Right-handed Takeshita.

326
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,833
Takaoka, with the sidearm.

327
00:17:24,916 --> 00:17:27,625
And left-handed Nojima.

328
00:17:27,708 --> 00:17:30,708
[OOYAMA] That trio of
third-years is all we need.

329
00:17:30,791 --> 00:17:32,458
I don't want to mess with
their motivation by giving

330
00:17:32,541 --> 00:17:35,583
a cocky first-year
special treatment.

331
00:17:35,666 --> 00:17:37,583
We gotta keep their
confidence up, you know?

332
00:17:37,666 --> 00:17:39,125
Keep 'em pitching with pride.

333
00:17:41,916 --> 00:17:45,000
--[TADASHI sighs] Okay...
--[OOYAMA] Hmm...?

334
00:17:45,083 --> 00:17:46,208
[TAKAOKA, NOJIMA, TAKESHITA]
Manager!

335
00:17:47,416 --> 00:17:49,041
Are you still not letting
Tachibana throw

336
00:17:49,125 --> 00:17:50,708
in the bullpen with us?

337
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:52,083
[OOYAMA]
Huh?

338
00:17:52,166 --> 00:17:53,541
We can't wait.

339
00:17:53,625 --> 00:17:56,666
We need him to start pithing
relief as soon as possible

340
00:17:56,750 --> 00:17:58,208
And, depending
on how good he is,

341
00:17:58,291 --> 00:18:01,291
I was thinking I could practice
defense in the outfield.

342
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:04,125
And I was thinking
I could try shortstop.

343
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:05,875
Hold on a minute.
You're upperclassmen.

344
00:18:05,958 --> 00:18:07,833
Wouldn't letting
a first-year pitch with you

345
00:18:07,916 --> 00:18:08,833
hurt your pride?

346
00:18:08,916 --> 00:18:10,333
Manager, lemme
ask you something:

347
00:18:10,416 --> 00:18:13,333
have you ever seen
Tachibana pitch?

348
00:18:13,416 --> 00:18:14,708
Well, no, I haven't.

349
00:18:14,791 --> 00:18:16,041
It's our third
year of high school,

350
00:18:16,125 --> 00:18:18,250
which means it's
our last summer!

351
00:18:18,333 --> 00:18:19,750
We want to stay in
the running for as long

352
00:18:19,833 --> 00:18:22,083
as we possibly can this season!

353
00:18:22,166 --> 00:18:23,916
Which means,
we wanna break our stupid,

354
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,166
20 year slump.

355
00:18:25,250 --> 00:18:27,166
We really wanna get
past the third round!

356
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:29,583
[GROUP]
Manager!

357
00:18:29,666 --> 00:18:31,916
Hey, Imagawa!

358
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,250
Yeah?

359
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:36,083
Get me the Tachibana brothers!

360
00:18:36,166 --> 00:18:37,333
[TADASHI grunts]

361
00:18:56,125 --> 00:18:57,375
[gasps]

362
00:19:09,208 --> 00:19:10,166
[TOUMA grunts]

363
00:19:11,583 --> 00:19:13,666
[OOYAMA gasps]

364
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:19,083
[OOYAMA] Were you ever planning
to tell me about Touma?

365
00:19:19,166 --> 00:19:20,083
[EISUKE]
Huh?

366
00:19:20,166 --> 00:19:21,666
[barks]

367
00:19:21,750 --> 00:19:23,833
[OOYAMA] The rumors don't even
come close to doing him justice!

368
00:19:23,916 --> 00:19:25,166
[EISUKE]
I've never heard 'em.

369
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:27,541
How should I know whether
they're right or not?

370
00:19:27,625 --> 00:19:29,125
The kid's incredible!

371
00:19:29,208 --> 00:19:32,458
You should brag about him more!
Made me look like a total moron!

372
00:19:32,541 --> 00:19:34,458
[EISUKE]
Hmm... Well, honestly.

373
00:19:34,541 --> 00:19:36,833
I've been pretty swamped
at work for a long time.

374
00:19:36,916 --> 00:19:39,916
So, I haven't made it
out to a game in forever.

375
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:41,583
So you're saying
my son's really

376
00:19:41,666 --> 00:19:42,875
that amazing of a pitcher?

377
00:19:42,958 --> 00:19:44,291
Hell yeah!

378
00:19:44,375 --> 00:19:46,583
I wouldn't believe he was
yours if I didn't know it.

379
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:48,416
Oh, yeah? Well, you're
the one who said that

380
00:19:48,500 --> 00:19:50,833
sometimes the apple falls
farther from the tree!

381
00:19:50,916 --> 00:19:52,208
Got me there!

382
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:54,250
In this case, the apple
got carried by a windstorm.

383
00:19:54,333 --> 00:19:56,500
More beer!
[laughs]

384
00:19:56,583 --> 00:19:57,791
--[TOUMA] Hey, I'm home.
--Yeah, me, too.

385
00:19:57,875 --> 00:19:58,791
[EISUKE yelling]

386
00:19:58,875 --> 00:20:00,416
Welcome back, you two.

387
00:20:02,375 --> 00:20:03,750
Doesn't that
old man ever drink beer

388
00:20:03,833 --> 00:20:05,500
at his own house?

389
00:20:07,958 --> 00:20:10,500
Haruka's not here,
just so you know.

390
00:20:10,583 --> 00:20:12,666
Guess the landlord
fixed their bath.

391
00:20:12,750 --> 00:20:16,791
Oh, really?
Well, I'm happy for them.

392
00:20:16,875 --> 00:20:17,958
[TOUMA]
Hey.

393
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,791
Can I go wash my hands now?

394
00:20:19,875 --> 00:20:20,875
Sir?

395
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:22,083
[SOUICHIROU growls]

396
00:20:22,166 --> 00:20:24,458
[PUNCH snickers]

397
00:20:24,541 --> 00:20:28,125
[OOYAMA, EISUKE] ♪ We pledge
our loyalty to you, ♪

398
00:20:28,208 --> 00:20:31,708
♪ dear, old Meisei High! ♪

399
00:20:31,791 --> 00:20:35,250
Yay! [laughing]
Here, here!

400
00:20:36,875 --> 00:20:39,500
[MAYUMI] Hmm. All right,
let's get dinner on the table.

401
00:20:39,583 --> 00:20:42,333
Otomi, tell your brothers
it's time to eat.

402
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:44,791
Yep!

403
00:20:44,875 --> 00:20:47,208
Oh, hey. Is Tou coming?

404
00:20:47,291 --> 00:20:50,583
No. He said he wanted to
lie down for a little while.

405
00:20:50,666 --> 00:20:51,958
That old man made
him pitch forever

406
00:20:52,041 --> 00:20:54,833
in the bullpen at
practice this afternoon.

407
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:57,000
I think Touma may
have overdone it a bit.

408
00:20:57,083 --> 00:20:59,708
Been a while since
he's thrown like that.

409
00:20:59,791 --> 00:21:01,166
Is he okay?

410
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:02,958
Of course,
he's fine, don't worry.

411
00:21:03,041 --> 00:21:06,333
He'll come down in a minute.
Come on, let's eat.

412
00:21:08,041 --> 00:21:09,625
[OTOMI]
I wanna check on him first.

413
00:21:11,625 --> 00:21:12,750
Leave him alone.

414
00:21:12,833 --> 00:21:14,791
I just told you he'll
be down in a minute.

415
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:17,625
I guess my word
alone's not enough.

416
00:21:17,708 --> 00:21:18,833
[PUNCH barks]

417
00:21:20,166 --> 00:21:23,166
[ISAMI] Those boys,
the Tachibana brothers.

418
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:25,416
How have they been doing lately?

419
00:21:25,500 --> 00:21:27,833
Sorry what?

420
00:21:27,916 --> 00:21:30,083
That girl...
How are her big brothers?

421
00:21:30,166 --> 00:21:32,000
[NISHIMURA]
Huh? Oh.

422
00:21:32,083 --> 00:21:33,833
They've got a new manager.

423
00:21:33,916 --> 00:21:36,166
Seems to be motivating
the entire team.

424
00:21:36,250 --> 00:21:39,291
[NISHIMURA]
Really? That's cool, I guess.

425
00:21:39,375 --> 00:21:42,791
But, like, they're still
just Meisei, right?

426
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:47,500
[ISAMI]
Yeah.

427
00:21:50,750 --> 00:21:52,375
[ISAMI]
Got that right.

428
00:23:31,375 --> 00:23:32,916
[OTOMI]
Next time, on <i>Mix</i> !

429
00:23:33,000 --> 00:23:34,875
[ARISA] Arisa here.
My big brother shows up

430
00:23:34,958 --> 00:23:36,083
in the next one.

431
00:23:36,166 --> 00:23:37,625
[OTOMI] Wait, who's
your big brother, again?

432
00:23:37,708 --> 00:23:39,083
[ARISA] Come on,
you don't even know that?

433
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:40,666
He was the driving force
behind last year's

434
00:23:40,750 --> 00:23:42,208
Koshien quarter finals!

435
00:23:42,291 --> 00:23:45,208
He's 6 feet tall, 172 pounds,
hits and throws left-handed,

436
00:23:45,291 --> 00:23:46,916
his blood type's B,
and he's so amazing that,

437
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:49,541
even in high school,
the pros are scouting him!

438
00:23:49,625 --> 00:23:51,416
[OTOMI]
Next time! "My Brother!"

439
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:54,375
So, what were you saying?

440
00:23:54,458 --> 00:23:55,458
[barks]

